Air Express
Through General Air Express, The Interline System, which includes
TWA and other leading air lines, a nation-wide network provides
for the fast dispatch of commodities by air to the major cities in the
United States.
Air Express affords an ideal means for the rapid distribution of
samples, quick replenishment of stocks and the development of new
markets. Store-door pickup and delivery is provided by the Postal
Telegraph Company. Packages weighing up to 200 pounds
will be
accepted and shipment made on a collect or a prepaid basis.
Through way bills permit air shipments to move over the group of
lines associated with TWA with a minimum
of time in transit.
Cargo insurance, offering full protection is available at low rates.
Call the nearest TWA, or Postal Telegraph office for rates and
detailed information.
